news.title: British Land sees strong rental growth; property value falls 4%
news.para: Aggressive rate hikes have hit the investment business of British landlords, even as strong operational performance has fuelled a tentative sector recovery from pandemic lows.

news.title: Sweden's SBB posts pre-tax loss of $287 million in Q3 2023
news.para: SBB, which owns properties across Sweden including hospitals and care homes, reported a pre-tax loss of 3.13 billion Swedish crowns ($287 million) for continuing operations, compared to a loss of a revised 2.56 billion a year ago.

news.title: India, ADB sign $400 million loan pact to build high-quality urban infrastructure
news.para: ​The signatories to the loan agreement for sub-programme 2 of the Sustainable Urban Development and Service Delivery Programme were Juhi Mukherjee, Joint Secretary, Department of Economic Affairs and Takeo Konishi, Country Director of ADB's India Resident Mission.

news.title: COWRKS opens 50,000 sq ft space in Chennai
news.para: Spread across 50,000 sq ft, the COWRKS' center offers 650 desks and is located in Millenia Business Park.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance aims to add 60 Roshni branches by FY24-end
news.para: PNB Housing Finance clocked in around Rs 750 crore disbursement under Roshni as on September 30, 2023, witnessing a growth of ~65% quarter-on-quarter.

news.title: WeWork refuses to sell India unit stake to Embassy; talks continue
news.para: WeWork India had offered to buy back the stake held by the parent company after the global counterpart sought insolvency protection under Chapter 11 of the US Bankruptcy Code earlier last month.

news.title: Asian Granito India posts net loss of Rs 2.80 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Asian Granito India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 402.12 crore in Q2 FY24 as against Rs 402.65 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: PCMC fines 421 construction sites for causing air pollution
news.para: Dedicated squads formed to initiate action against construction firms have issued notices for various violations at 421 sites in the last four days, and fines worth over Rs 33 lakh collectively have also been recovered from offenders.

news.title: Over 140 property registration offices in Maharashtra need relocation: Survey
news.para: Most of the offices identified for relocation are on the first floor, without lifts and are difficult to access, an official from the state registration department said.

news.title: Teething issues mar property data digitisation drive of Mangaluru civic body
news.para: Many property owners have raised concern about the need to re-submit copies of documents, such as building completion certificates, occupancy certificates, building licences, and khata or title deeds, to the MCC.

news.title: Bombay HC clears way for man to get home 48 years after grandfather was evicted
news.para: According to 34-year-old Ravindra Bhatuse's petition, in November 1975, his grandfather was issued notice to vacate his 106-square-foot room in Zenab Manzil, Byculla, and sent to Antop Hill transit camp.

news.title: Don't interfere in redevelopment of housing society: Bombay HC to Shanti Enterprises
news.para: Swashray CHS, Borivli (West), which has 16 members, had approached the HC saying it had lost faith in Shanti Enterprises and had thus terminated the deal with him for redevelopment.

news.title: Warburg Pincus makes Rs 600 crore exit from joint realty development platform with Runwal
news.para: In 2019, in one of the largest real-estate investment platform transactions in India, an affiliate of the New York-based institutional investor had entered into the alliance to develop shopping malls in key cities with a sizeable population and growing disposable incomes.

news.title: MahaRERA recovers over Rs 133 crore from defaulting builders
news.para: The regulatory authority had issued 1,053 warrants to recover ₹627.70 crore from developers for delay in the handing over of the apartments, with a warning to freeze their bank accounts and attach assets.

news.title: Homebuyers complain, EOW files FIR against ATS Infrastructure, directors
news.para: Around 1,860 people claimed to have been cheated of Rs 12.9 crore causing mental agony and economic distress to those who invested in the said project. No arrest has been made and investigations are underway, police said.

news.title: Three wards contribute 60% of Thane municipality's property tax collection
news.para: Data on property tax collections reveals that the corporation managed to collect Rs 429 crore by October end and is likely to touch its tax collection target for this fiscal year.

news.title: Cases of dumping building material on footpaths double in Nagpur
news.para: Data provided by Nagpur Municipal Corporation’s nuisance detection squad for 2018 indicates that 4,747 people (including individuals and builders) were fined Rs 77.46 lakh for stocking construction material at public places. In 2023 (till October), 8,428 people were penalised who paid a whopping fine of Rs 1.92 crore.

news.title: Anant Raj to raise up to Rs 500 crore
news.para: Anant Raj had reported a 79 per cent increase in its consolidated net profit to Rs 60.37 crore during the quarter ended September 30, 2023. It had registered net profit of Rs 33.74 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

news.title: China Fortune Land to set up $3.5 billion trust fund to help pay debt
news.para: The move is part of a debt restructuring plan unveiled in October 2021 with the debt-ridden developer seeking various ways to ease a liquidity crunch.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to make water meters a must for new constructions
news.para: The result of a water consumption survey in the Dum Dum-Cossipore belt has prompted the civic brass to take forward the scheme of installation of such meters at several other neighbourhoods across the Kolkata.
